            <p>Philad<hi rend="sup">a</hi> April 10<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1883<lb/></p>
            <p>Revd. S. Morais.<lb/>
                Sir&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>I am instructed to forward you<lb/> the following extract from the Minutes of the Board<lb/> of Managers of the &#34;Heb. Education Society&#44;&#34; being a part<lb/> of their proceedings at a meeting held this day.<lb/></p>
            <p>&#34;Mr Allen having volunteered through Mr<lb/> Newhouse to continue for a short period his services<lb/> in Case no teacher was procured for the School of<lb/> the Heb. Education Society&#44; the following resolution<lb/> offered by Jos. Newhouse &#38; seconded by A. T. Jones was<lb/> unanimously adopted&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Resolved&#44; That the offer of Mr M M Allen to continue<lb/> his services as Teacher be accepted until the Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi><lb/> Mr DeSolla is enabled to assume the duties of that<lb/> office&#44; he being allowed such compensation as the<lb/> School Directors may deem proper&#44; and that<lb/> should occasion require the Board will thankfully<lb/> accept the kindly offered services of the Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi> S Morais.&#34;<lb/></p>
            <p>With sentiments of high esteem I am<lb/> Resp<hi rend="sup">y</hi> Yours<lb/> Alfred T Jones<lb/> Sec<hi rend="sup">y</hi> H. Ed. So.<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
